# AI Resume Screener — Project Context

Full-stack RAG chat: ask natural-language questions about a collection of CV PDFs → LangGraph agents retrieve grounded chunks → answer with source citations.

## Stack

| Layer | Tech |
|---|---|
| Frontend | Vite 6 · React 19 · TypeScript strict · Tailwind CSS v4 · shadcn/ui · Plus Jakarta Sans |
| Backend | FastAPI · LangGraph · Python 3.11+ |
| LLM | Google Gemini `gemini-2.0-flash` |
| Embeddings | Google `text-embedding-004` |
| Vector store | ChromaDB (local, persistent) |
| PDF extraction | pymupdf4llm |
| CV generation | Seed JSON · ReportLab · `scripts/generate_cvs.py` (no LLM) |

## Two LangGraph agents

```
ingest_agent:   extract_text → chunk_by_section → embed → store_chroma → verify_index
chat_agent:     retrieve → validate_context → generate_answer → cite_sources
```

CV PDFs are generated offline from `data/seed/profiles.json` — not via LangGraph.

## Key files

- `data/seed/profiles.json` — 28 hand-crafted demo candidates
- `scripts/generate_cvs.py` — seed → PDF + manifest
- `backend/app/cv_renderer.py` — ReportLab PDF builder
- `backend/app/agents/ingest_agent.py` — offline RAG indexing
- `backend/app/agents/chat_agent.py` — runtime Q&A with grounded citations
- `backend/app/invariants.py` — runtime guards (`InvariantError`)
- `backend/app/metrics.py` — `RunMetrics` + `Timer` per node
- `backend/app/rag/` — chunker, store, retriever
- `frontend/src/hooks/use-chat.ts` — chat state, send, cancel
- `frontend/src/lib/api.ts` — typed API client + `ApiError`
- `frontend/src/types/api.ts` — mirrors `backend/app/schemas/chat.py` (camelCase)

## Architecture docs

- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — agent flows, data layout, API surface
- `docs/DEVELOPMENT.md` — commit workflow, local setup, testing

## Non-obvious constraints

- Chat must never hallucinate: `validate_context` blocks answers when max retrieval score < threshold.
- `check_sources_from_retrieved` ensures every citation maps to a real chunk.
- ChromaDB path `data/chroma/` is gitignored; PDFs in `data/cvs/` are committed for demo.
- Agents are compiled once and cached per module.
- Frontend types in `types/api.ts` must stay in sync with `schemas/chat.py`.
- Tests: `cd backend && pytest -v` from project root with `PYTHONPATH=.` or `pytest.ini`.
